anreview7\">Sightseeing</a> by Rattawut Lapcharoensap</p> <h2> 2004</h2> <p> <strong><strong>Winner:</strong></strong> <a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/books/2004/may/22/highereducation.scienceandnature\">Mutants: On the Form, Varieties and Errors of the Human Body</a> by Armand Marie Leroi</p> <p> <strong><strong>Shortlist:<br /></strong></strong><a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/books/2004/apr/10/featuresreviews.guardianreview6\">Ground Water</a> by Matthew Hollis <br /><a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/books/2004/aug/21/featuresreviews.guardianreview8\">Natasha</a> by David Bezmozgis<br /><a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/books/2004/oct/02/featuresreviews.guardianreview20\">Jonathan Strange and Mr Norrell</a> by Susanna Clarke<br /><a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/books/2004/nov/06/featuresreviews.guardianreview37\">The Places in Between</a> by Rory Stewart</p> <h2><strong><strong>2003</strong></strong></h2> <p> <strong><strong>Winner: </strong></strong><a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/books/2003/may/11/guardianfirstbookaward2003.guardianfirstbookaward\">Mountains of the Mind</a> by Robert Macfarlane</p> <p><strong><strong>Shortlist:<br /></strong></strong><a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/books/2003/jun/14/featuresreviews.guardianreview20\">Brick Lane</a> by Monica Ali<br /><a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/books/2003/jun/07/guardianfirstbookaward2003.biography\">Stasiland</a> by Anna Funder<br /><a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/books/2003/jan/18/featuresreviews.guardianreview18\">Vernon God Little</a> by DBC Pierre<br /><a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/books/2003/jun/14/featuresreviews.guardianreview32\">Into The Silent Land</a> by Paul Broks</p> <h2> 2002</h2> <p> <strong><strong>Winner:</strong></strong> <a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/books/2002/jun/08/featuresreviews.guardianreview28\">Everything is Illuminated</a> by Jonathan Safran Foer</p> <p><strong><strong>Shortlist:<br /></strong></strong><a href=\"http://www.th